                                                            BUSINESSS QUESTION
Where are we losing customers in the purchase journey (drop-off)?

                          QUERY
SELECT
CASE
    WHEN cart_abandonment_rate > 20 THEN 'High Drop-off'
    WHEN cart_abandonment_rate > 10 THEN 'Medium Drop-off'
    ELSE 'Low Drop-off'
END AS dropoff_level,
COUNT(*) AS customer_count
FROM ecommerce_data
GROUP BY dropoff_level;

INSIGHT
Many customers fall into the high drop-off group, which means many customers are leaving before completing their purchase. This shows there
is a problem in the checkout or decision stage.


RECOMMENDATION:
Display all costs early in the shopping process to avoid last-minute surprises, Reduce the number of steps in the checkout process, Accept a rang
of payment methods

